            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Related behavior occurs when creating a floating window B, with cleared highlighting, over another floating window A. The background for floating window B inherits that of the bottom non-floating window, rather than that of floating window A.\r\n\r\n```vim\r\n\" Create a new tab\r\n:tabe\r\n\r\n\" Create a floating window A\r\n:let opts1 = {'relative': 'editor', 'width': 30, 'height': 20, 'col': 5, 'row': 5, 'zindex': 100}\r\n:let bufnr1 = nvim_create_buf(v:false, v:true)\r\n:let win1 = nvim_open_win(bufnr1, 0, opts1)\r\n\r\n\" Create a floating window B above the prior floating window, with cleared highlighting\r\n:let opts2 = {'relative': 'editor', 'width': 20, 'height': 10, 'col': 10, 'row': 10, 'zindex': 200, 'border': 'single'}\r\n:let bufnr2 = nvim_create_buf(v:false, v:true)\r\n:let win2 = nvim_open_win(bufnr2, 0, opts2)\r\n:highlight clear Highlight\r\n:call nvim_win_set_option(win2, 'winhighlight', 'Normal:Highlight')\r\n```\r\n\r\n| Actual | Expected |\r\n| :-----:|:-------: |\r\n| ![actual](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/541289/ad5133e0-af6e-4cde-af7f-2398f4f73b37) | ![expected](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/541289/8fb4e26a-1794-49ee-ab04-2349fabfeedc) |\r\n\r\n",
